Identifying Age-Related Conditions¶

What¶

The objective of this project is to develop a predictive model that can determine whether a person has any of three specific medical conditions. The task involves classifying individuals into two groups: Class 1, which signifies the presence of one or more of the three medical conditions, and Class 0, indicating the absence of any of these conditions. The model will be trained using health characteristic measurements.

Why¶

Traditionally, identifying these medical conditions requires a lengthy and invasive process of gathering information directly from patients. However, with the implementation of predictive models, we can streamline this process by collecting essential health characteristics related to the conditions and encoding them while ensuring the privacy and confidentiality of patient data.

How¶

We will do Lasso Regression, Regression Tree, Neural Network, and XGBoosted Random Forest

First we need to figure out how to measure how good our model is. We use the balanced_log_loss model

In [98]:
from sklearn.metrics import log_loss
def balanced_log_loss(y_test, y_pred):
    nc = np.bincount(y_test)
    return log_loss(y_test, y_pred, sample_weight = 1/nc[y_test], eps=1e-7)
